review_blob:
Appearance: Clear, hardly any head.
Taste: Not a whole lot there.  Watery and light.  Not a strong finish.
Mouthfeel: Medium-Bodied
Drinkability: Not a strong contenter with the other greats out there!  Too easy to forget.

From the Brewery:  Missoula, MT.  A great overall flavor and a lasting aftertaste.  Has a good head that is off white in color.  A strong aroma but not too strong to overpower the taste.  A tad malty and very bitter hops, great alcohol percentage!  One of my favorites!

From a draft at the brewery.  Brown-black body with beige head. Not as thick as you would think going down but very tasty.  Aroma is moderately sweet, butterscotch, caramel,  scotch, smokey. Taste is moderately sweet, caramel, smoke. Medium body, light stickiness
beer_name: Kettle House Cold Smoke Scotch Ale
